# Sprint 2: Sanglogium Case Study Page — 14 Sections, Sticky Nav, Scroll Reveal

## UX Flows

1. [Page load]: User clicks Sanglogium link → arrives at `/projects/sanglogium/` → sees Hero section at top
2. [Scroll]: User scrolls down → Hero scrolls out of view → sticky horizontal pill nav appears at top → nav shows all 13 content section names (hero excluded)
3. [Nav click]: User clicks nav pill → page smooth-scrolls to that section → pill highlights active section
4. [Section reveal]: User scrolls through sections → each section fades in and slides up as it enters viewport
5. [Mobile]: User on mobile → sticky nav is horizontally scrollable pill row; active pill auto-scrolls into horizontal view → sections stack single-column → screenshots above text
6. [Reduced motion]: User has `prefers-reduced-motion` → sections render at full opacity immediately → no fade/slide animation
7. [No JS]: User has JS disabled → all sections visible at full opacity immediately (default CSS state is visible; JS applies hidden class before observer fires)

## End-State Overview

A single long-scroll case study page with 14 `<section>` elements covering the Sang Logium e-commerce platform. Desktop shows alternating two-column layouts. Mobile stacks to single column. A sticky horizontal nav appears after the hero, highlighting the active section via Intersection Observer. Each section fades in on scroll. All section text content uses `[Content TBD]` placeholders — real copy is added by the human after the portfolio is built. Screenshots use Astro's `<Image>` component.

## Architecture Contract

- **Page**: Single `sanglogium.astro` file, no pagination
- **Sections**: 14 `<section>` elements with `id` attributes; Footer CTA is a separate `<footer>` element
- **Sticky nav**: `position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 10`; appears after hero scrolls past via `IntersectionObserver` on hero
- **Active tracking**: `IntersectionObserver` with `threshold: 0.1` on each section → updates nav `aria-current`
- **Scroll reveal**: `IntersectionObserver` on each content section → toggles CSS class; initial CSS state is `opacity: 1; transform: none` so content is visible without JS; JS adds a `js-reveal-pending` class to sections before starting the observer (applied only when JS runs), then removes it when section enters viewport
- **Images**: Astro `<Image>` component; hero image: `loading="eager" fetchpriority="high"`; all others: `loading="lazy"`
- **Responsive**: Desktop 2-column alternating, mobile single column via Tailwind
- **ClientRouter lifecycle**: All IntersectionObserver setup inside `document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', ...)`, teardown (`observer.disconnect()` for all observers) inside `document.addEventListener('astro:before-swap', ...)`
- **Hash navigation**: Each nav anchor calls `e.preventDefault()` then reads `anchor.hash` (e.g. `"#overview"`) and calls `document.querySelector(anchor.hash).scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' })` — uses `anchor.hash` not `anchor.href` to avoid full-URL querySelector failure
- **Scroll-margin-top**: All 14 `<section>` elements have `scroll-margin-top: 5rem` (80px) so titles are fully visible below sticky nav after anchor clicks

### File contracts
- `src/pages/projects/sanglogium.astro` — long-scroll page
- `src/components/FeatureSection.astro` — reusable: accepts `title`, `description`, `reversed` (boolean) props; 2-column desktop layout; `slot="visual"` + `slot="text"`
- `src/components/StickyNav.astro` — horizontal pill nav, accepts `sections` array prop

